#-## 
#-## Mount the ISO image of CentOS/6.3/279 here. Use following commands to expose the contents of the ISO image:
#-##
#-##  At Linux command line: 
#-##      mount -o loop -t iso9660 /home/kpCloud/os/iso/<iso_name>.iso /home/kpCloud/os/src/CentOS/6.3/279
#-##
#-##      OR
#-##
#-##  add following stanza into /etc/fstab followed by 'mount -a' in order to survive reboots as well:
#-##      /home/kpCloud/os/iso/CentOS/<iso_name>.iso	/home/kpCloud/os/src/CentOS/6.3/279	iso9660	loop	0 0
#-##
#-##
#-##  If any one of the choice is selected then this file will get hidden by that mount command until it is unmount.
#-##
#-##
